What I think is missing from the documents is the fact that **if you are importing the scss version**, then you need to have postcss installed and configured. AND you also need an rtl plugin. I had success with [postcss-rtlcss](https://github.com/elchininet/postcss-rtlcss).

So just install postcss & postcss-rtlcss:

`npm i -D postcss postcss-rtlcss`

Then in your project root (or in the app dir if you are using nx) add this config file named `postcss.config.js`:

```
module.exports = {
  plugins: ['postcss-rtlcss']
};
```
And now you just run your project and should have rtl working perfectly!

