For customizing heading fonts, I create a css variable for $headings-font-family in my customized Bootstrap with SASS, using the default --bs-font-sans-serif variable as fallback. (https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.2/customize/sass/#file-structure_

In my custom bootstrap.scss, I add this:

 ```
 // default variable overrides...
$headings-font-family: var(--headings-font-family), var(--bs-font-sans-serif);
@import '../../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/bootstrap';
```

This allows me to change the default headings font-family easily in my theme's css by defining --headings-font-family. Such as in the following:

theme.css
```
:root {
	--headings-font-family: 'trashhand';
}

@font-face {
	font-family: 'trashhand';
	src: url('../fonts/trashhand/trashhand-webfont.woff2') format('woff2'), url('../fonts/trashhand-webfont.woff') format('woff');
	font-display: swap;
}
```
