Not sure whether you want to

1. fix the position of the carousel below the content; Or,
2. be scrollable with the content.

Let me assume case (1):

- Put the carousel `position: fixed; top: 0;`, so the element stick to the top of the screen.
- Set the main-container `z-index: 100` rather than "auto", so the content can display above the carousel element.
- :key: Set the main-container `position: relative`, so it display in higher priority relatively.
- Set the margin for main-container, so the content won't overlap with the carousel buttons.

Here's the code:

```css
.main-container {
	position: relative;
	margin-left: 15%;
	margin-right: 15%;
	z-index: 100;
}

#carouselExampleControls {
	position: fixed;
	top: 0;
}
```

Please see a demo for reference: https://codepen.io/Edditoria/details/oNdeZNg

However, for case (1), you will need to add more styles for the images, i.e. scaling and position.

