Bootstrap is usually used for responsive design across devices and has "standard" size and spacing. In my knowledge, it does not have settings to fit your need.

For your case, if showing first and last column is acceptable. You can make they sticky. Something like:

```css
.table-sticky-header thead {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  background: white;
}

.table-sticky-footer tfoot {
  position: sticky;
  bottom: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  background: white;
}

.table-sticky-first-col thead th:first-child {
  position: sticky;
  left: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  background: white;
}

.table-sticky-first-col tbody th {
  position: sticky;
  left: 0;
  background: white;
}

.table-sticky-last-col thead th:last-child {
  position: sticky;
  right: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  background: white;
}

.table-sticky-last-col tbody td:last-child {
  position: sticky;
  right: 0;
  background: white;
}
```

NOTE: The first column is `<th>` rather than `<td>`.

It is a starter code, btw. You may change more styles for your need.

