For what it's worth, I did some testing, and for folks like me who are compiling Bootstrap **separately** (e.g. as a second standalone entrypoint in Webpack), if I import `root` or `reboot` again in my main site Sass (or anything past `utilities` in [the framework bootstrap.scss file](https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/v5.3.2/scss/bootstrap.scss) for that matter), then that results in duplicated Bootstrap CSS in my compiled main site CSS, and it also results in significantly slower Sass compilation time, even if I only make a change in my main site Sass.

To clarify, this is my scenario:

```
// Entry for Webpack bundling process
entry: [
    // Full Bootstrap framework Sass, with my variable customization
    "./assets/src/styles/bootstrap/bootstrap.scss",
    // Main site Sass - this should have access Bootstrap Sass variables, but shouldn't have ANY compiled Bootstrap framework CSS
    "./assets/src/styles/main.scss"
]
```

If I import `root` in `main.scss`, then I get duplicated Bootstrap `:root` variables in my compiled main site CSS (because they were already compiled and included by the first `bootstrap` Webpack entrypoint). If I stop at `utilities`, that seems to be the sweet spot—then I have full access to all of the Bootstrap Sass vars/maps in my main Sass, but none of the core Bootstrap CSS gets duplicated.

So it seems like this is the correct set up for Bootstrap imports when you just want access to the Bootstrap Sass variables/maps but don't want any actual Bootstrap CSS:

```
// Bootstrap functions
@import "~bootstrap/scss/functions";

// Bootstrap variable customization
@import "bootstrap-variables";

// Bootstrap variable defaults
@import "~bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "~bootstrap/scss/variables-dark";

// Bootstrap map customization
@import "bootstrap-maps";

// Remaining Bootstrap imports
@import "~bootstrap/scss/maps";
@import "~bootstrap/scss/mixins";
@import "~bootstrap/scss/utilities";

// DO NOT IMPORT ANY OF THESE
// @import "~bootstrap/scss/root";
// @import "~bootstrap/scss/reboot";
// @import "~bootstrap/scss/type";
```

