Sorry @crespire, forgot to answer this question:

> However, is there a reason why `getInstance` doesn't work in this case? It does seem to behave with `getOrCreateInstance`.

The instance is only created after having clicked on the button which triggers the creation and the rendering of the modal. 
In the internal code of Bootstrap's modals:

```js
EventHandler.on(document, EVENT_CLICK_DATA_API, SELECTOR_DATA_TOGGLE, function (event) {
   // ...
   const data = Modal.getOrCreateInstance(target)
   // ...
}
```

It's not maybe the best event to attach it in my example, but just to show you the difference, here is [a CodePen getting the instance as you did but only when the modal is displayed (so after on the button's click event)](https://codepen.io/julien-deramond/pen/YzBXJEQ). This time, you can use `getInstance()` because it has already been created by Bootstrap when you clicked on the button.

```js
const triggerButton = document.getElementById('triggerButton').addEventListener('click', event => {
  const modal = bootstrap.Modal.getInstance('#data-attribute-modal');
  console.log(modal) // this is not `null` you can get the instance
}

const modal = bootstrap.Modal.getInstance('#data-attribute-modal');
console.log(modal) // this is `null` because the instance is not yet created when the page is loaded, nobody clicked on the button
```

