}
```

the generated CSS will be:

```css
.p-4, .custom-class {
  padding: 1.5rem !important;
}

.text-white, .custom-class {
  --bs-text-opacity: 1;
  color: rgba(var(--bs-white-rgb), var(--bs-text-opacity)) !important;
}

.bg-primary, .custom-class {
  --bs-bg-opacity: 1;
  background-color: rgba(var(--bs-primary-rgb), var(--bs-bg-opacity)) !important;
}
```

So your `.custom-class` will contains some `!important` you might not want, depending on the use cases and your objectives with this class.

Instead, you could do something like:

```scss
.custom-class {
  background-color: $primary;
  color: $white;
  padding: map-get($spacers, 4);
}
```

