As Julien mentioned, the issue is more likely related to your paths config for Vite. I encountered similar issues before and the core problem was in the configuration of the [base url](https://vite.dev/config/shared-options.html#base) in the vite.config file, its relation to your assets location and how you import them in your components.

In addition, Vite does not resolve CSS paths by default. You might need to set up a custom resolve that might look like the following:
```jsx
import path from 'path';

export default defineConfig({
//  ... the rest of your configuration
resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),
    },
  },
});

```

In CSS, paths would look like the following:

```css
background: url(@/assets/icons/icon-time.svg) no-repeat;
```

So:
- Check the `base` value in Vite config
- Use path aliases and absolute path imports when possible
- Update path resolve in Vite configuration

